title_s: Possible HTTP Command and Control to Multiple Endpoints
summary_s:
The device 100.11.111.16 was observed making repeated HTTP connections to a range of rare external endpoints, with the same user agent string.

Moreover, this device only used this user agent string for connections to a limited set of endpoints - suggesting that the activity was initiated by a standalone software process as opposed to a web browser.

If such behaviour is unexpected, further investigation may be required to determine if this activity represents malicious command and control as opposed to legitimate telemetry of some form.
summaryFirstSentence_s: The device 100.11.111.16 was observed making repeated HTTP connections to a range of rare external endpoints, with the same user agent string.
